:session a schema:Event ;
    schema:name "Session 2026-06-15 (Claude Sonnet 4.6 + Claude Code — OKF SPARQL Accordion URL Fix + Step 50 Memory Write)"@en ;
    schema:description "Fixed 6 broken SPARQL accordion run buttons in okf-google-cloud-blog-infographic.html (Q1, Q2, Q3 — each with display code block + href). Root causes: (1) relative PREFIX IRI <okf-open-knowledge-format-ontology.ttl#okf-> invalid at remote endpoint, replaced with absolute DAV IRI; (2) missing FROM <DAV-graph-IRI> clause per Step 41. Added Step 50 (:step-sparqlAbsolutePrefixIRI) to preferences.ttl encoding the absolute-PREFIX-IRI rule. Created companion howto/sparql-absolute-prefix-iri.ttl."@en ;
    schema:startDate "2026-06-15T00:00:00Z"^^xsd:dateTime ;
    schema:agent <https://linkedin.com/in/kidehen#this> ;
    schema:hasPart :taskFixSparqlAccordions, :taskWriteStep50, :taskEnrichInstanceData, :taskFixWhatIsOKFHrefs, :taskFixRemainingGitHubIRIs, :taskAddHowToSection, :taskFixFAQAnchors, :taskFixGlossaryDefs .

:taskFixSparqlAccordions a schema:Action ;
    schema:name "Fix 6 SPARQL accordion buttons in okf-google-cloud-blog-infographic.html"@en ;
    schema:description "Three queries (Q1: table joins, Q2: metric documents, Q3: KnowledgeBundle + DBpedia SERVICE federation) each had two broken targets: sparql-code display block and sparql-run-btn href. Fixed both per query. Changes per query: (1) absolute DAV IRI for okf: PREFIX, (2) SELECT DISTINCT, (3) FROM <...instance-data.ttl> before WHERE. Note: Q3 will still return zero rows because schema:provider is absent from the instance data TTL — the syntactic break is resolved, the data gap is out of scope."@en ;
    schema:object <../../../../../LLMs/Claude%20Generated/webpages/okf-google-cloud-blog-infographic.html> ;
    schema:result "6 edits applied successfully. SPARQL Run buttons now point to valid absolute DAV IRIs with correct graph scoping."@en .

:taskWriteStep50 a schema:Action ;
    schema:name "Write Step 50 (sparqlAbsolutePrefixIRI) to preferences.ttl + companion HowTo"@en ;
    schema:description "Appended :step-sparqlAbsolutePrefixIRI (position 50) and :topicSparqlAbsolutePrefixIRI to preferences.ttl. Created agent-rdf-memory/howto/sparql-absolute-prefix-iri.ttl with 5 steps explaining the root cause, derivation procedure, dual-target fix, FROM clause requirement, and post-fix verification."@en ;
    schema:result "preferences.ttl updated; howto/sparql-absolute-prefix-iri.ttl created."@en .

:taskEnrichInstanceData a schema:Action ;
    schema:name "Enrich instance-data TTL with row-level records and rewrite 3 SPARQL accordions"@en ;
    schema:description "Two-part task: (1) Fixed broken relative @prefix okf: IRI in okf-open-knowledge-format-instance-data.ttl (Step 50 violation) and appended SECTION 10 — 8 class/property declarations (okf:OrderRecord, okf:CustomerRecord, okf:orderId, okf:customerId, okf:orderDate, okf:revenueUSD, okf:customerName, okf:email, okf:signupDate, okf:isRowOf) plus 5 CustomerRecord instances (CUST001–CUST005) and 10 OrderRecord instances across 2 calendar weeks (Week 1: 2026-06-01 to 2026-06-07 / WAU=4; Week 2: 2026-06-08 to 2026-06-14 / WAU=4). (2) Rewrote all 3 SPARQL accordions in okf-google-cloud-blog-infographic.html: Q1 = JOIN query (OrderRecord x CustomerRecord via shared okf:customerId); Q2 = COUNT(DISTINCT ?custId) WAU metric for Week 1 with xsd:date FILTER; Q3 = SUM(?revenue) GROUP BY customer for revenue ranking. All queries conform to Step 41 (FROM clause), Step 50 (absolute PREFIX IRI), Step 28 (SELECT → text/x-html+tr)."@en ;
    schema:object <../../../../../LLMs/Claude%20Generated/rdf/okf-open-knowledge-format-instance-data.ttl>,
                  <../../../../../LLMs/Claude%20Generated/webpages/okf-google-cloud-blog-infographic.html> ;
    schema:result "Instance data TTL enriched with 5 customers + 10 orders. All 3 accordion queries now operate on computable row-level data. Run buttons use valid absolute DAV PREFIX IRIs, FROM clauses, and correct SELECT format."@en .

:taskFixWhatIsOKFHrefs a schema:Action ;
    schema:name "Fix 7 fabricated GitHub IRIs in 'What is OKF?' section"@en ;
    schema:description "Replaced 7 entity hrefs that pointed to GitHub repository URLs (https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/knowledge-catalog/tree/main/okf#...) with resolver-wrapped IRIs sourced from the companion TTL files per Step 49. Card entities (ConceptDocument, KnowledgeBundle, EnrichmentAgent, Visualizer) map to ontology class IRIs in okf-open-knowledge-format-ontology.ttl using the #okf-{ClassName} fragment pattern. Design principle entities (PrincipleMinimallyOpinionated, PrincipleProducerConsumerIndependence, PrincipleFormatNotPlatform) map to instance data IRIs in okf-open-knowledge-format-instance-data.ttl. All resolver URLs use the pattern: https://linkeddata.uriburner.com/describe/?url={percent-encoded-DAV-IRI}. Post-fix grep confirmed zero GitHub fabricated IRIs remain in the file."@en ;
    schema:object <../../../../../LLMs/Claude%20Generated/webpages/okf-infographic-claude_sonnet_4_6-1.html> ;
    schema:result "7 edits applied. No GitHub IRIs remain. All entity hrefs now resolve to DAV-hosted RDF entities via the URIBurner resolver."@en .

