    schema:result "All 7 glossary definition divs now hyperlinked to companion TTL entity IRIs via URIBurner resolver."@en .

:lessonSparqlRelativeIRI a schema:Thing ;
    schema:name "Lesson: relative PREFIX IRIs in SPARQL are silently broken at remote endpoints"@en ;
    schema:description "A PREFIX IRI like <filename.ttl#fragment> is resolved by the remote SPARQL endpoint relative to its own base URL, not the filesystem. The resulting absolute IRI points to a non-existent resource. The failure is silent — the endpoint returns 0 results rather than an error. The fix is always to use the absolute DAV IRI derived from the skills contract DAV path pattern."@en .

:lessonMemoryProtocolEnforcement a schema:Thing ;
    schema:name "Lesson: Agent RDF Memory Protocol failure causes compounding SPARQL URL bugs"@en ;
    schema:description "The root systemic cause of the SPARQL accordion breakage was failure to execute the mandatory Agent RDF Memory Protocol (Steps 28 and 41 of preferences.ttl) before generating the HTML. Had Step 41 (virtuosoWorkbenchQueryDedup) and Step 28 (virtuosoSparqlFormats) been read before generation, the relative IRI and missing FROM clause errors would not have occurred. The protocol is a blocking gate, not a post-hoc check."@en .
